nodes.title: !! Important Info!!
widgets_values:
If several variants are enabled, the lowest one is used.

If no extra image is enabled, the image from the load image group is used.

Standard:
The strength is controlled via the influence reduction, between 0.01 and 0.2 are good values

Mix prompt: 
Standard must be enabled, the strength is controlled via the influence 
reduction, between 0.01 and 0.5

Mix Recommended:
Redux  Conditioning Start 0
                    End 0.01 to 0.3
Prompt Conditioning Start 0 to 0.3
                    End 1

Redux advanced: 
Standard and mix prompt should be disabled

Mask only works with Redux Advanced!

If mask is enabled but no mask has been defined, Redux advanced cannot work!

nodes.title: Info Workflow
widgets_values: If the Load Image group is switched on, the sizes for generation are approximated to the loaded image, or you can select a new size at the top, in which case the image will be cropped. For pure text to image, you can set the size directly in the Base Settings, but the Load Image group must be switched off. Inpaint works the same as for image to image. You can also combine both, but please note that the Load Image switch is not switched off when you switch off Image to Image, although this deactivates the Load image group. Little Bug in den Custom Nodes.

nodes.title: Model Sampling Flux Infos
widgets_values:
How the ModelSamplingFlux Parameters Work Together:

Max Shift sets the possible maximum flexibility. Standard 1.15
Base Shift sets the starting flexibility. Standard 0.50

Summary:
High Shift: More potential for adding new details and sharpness, but with an increased risk of noise and artifacts.
Low Shift: More controlled and potentially cleaner images with less risk of noise, but possibly less detail and sharpness.

CLIPTextEncodeFlux:
1.02.0 Very weak guidance 
 Model ignores parts of the prompt. Abstract art, experiments.
2.53.5 Balanced 
 Slight stylization, but recognizable prompt implementation. 
Standard for Flux (e.g., landscapes).
4.05.0 Strong guidance 
 More precise details, but less "artistic flow." 
Legible text, clear objects.
> 5.0 Overfitting risk 
 Unnaturally hard edges/artifacts. Only for special cases (e.g., logos).

nodes.title: Standard Nunchaku workflow Models preselected V7.0
Settings Apply Controlnet
widgets_values:
Upscale: use none
 Canny: use cv2.Canny,           controlnet_conditioning_scale=0.7, control_guidance_end=0.8.
 Soft Edge: use AnylineDetector, controlnet_conditioning_scale=0.7, control_guidance_end=0.8.
 Depth: use depth-anything,      controlnet_conditioning_scale=0.8, control_guidance_end=0.8.
 Pose: use DWPose,               controlnet_conditioning_scale=0.9, control_guidance_end=0.65.
 Gray: use cv2.cvtColor,         controlnet_conditioning_scale=0.9, control_guidance_end=0.8.

Download the Nunchaku FLUX.1 model from 
https://huggingface.co/mit-han-lab/nunchaku-flux.1-dev to `models/diffusion_models`. 
txt2img or img2img:
For NVIDIA 30/40-series GPUs -> svdq-int4-flux.1-dev or svdq-int4-flux.1-schnell
For NVIDIA 50-series GPUs    -> svdq-fp4-flux.1-dev or svdq-fp-flux.1-schnell

Only enable this option if ControlNet is to be used.

Important: When ControlNet is enabled, an image must always be loaded, either via standard input at the beginning or directly alongside the ControlNet models.
